---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="about" description="About parrik — a home for essays on distributed systems, biology, and the practice.">
  <article class="about">
    <p class="lede">
      parrik is a home for essays on distributed systems, epistemics,
      biology, and the practice. Three essays are up. The rest is slowly
      arriving.
    </p>

    <p>
      The through-line is signal-responsive systems. Code, bodies, the way
      we think about our own lives. When the signal comes loose from the
      context it was meant to serve, failure can look rational from the
      inside — a memory structure that collapses the difference between
      repetition and corroboration; a cell that has lost the tissue-level
      broadcast it was meant to answer to; a PR sitting in front of a
      reviewer who does not understand why it matters. Different surfaces,
      same shape. The writing tries to name the shape where it finds it.
    </p>

    <h2>Shelf</h2>

    <p>
      Distributed systems: Martin Kleppmann, Marc Brooker, Kyle Kingsbury
      (Jepsen), Dan Luu, Hillel Wayne. Epistemics: Julia Galef's Scout
      Mindset. Biology is where the analogies come from. FKJ is the sonic
      anchor for practice.
    </p>

    <h2>Method</h2>

    <p>
      <em>Attribution is not confidence.</em> A claim repeated five times
      is not five pieces of evidence — it is one derivation restated five
      times. Real confidence comes from independent derivations. This is
      the load-bearing rule of the
      <a href="https://github.com/parrik/know-thyself">Know Thyself
      scaffold</a> and the background discipline of the essay shelf.
    </p>

    <h2>Currently</h2>

    <p>
      Writing the next essay. Reading DDIA Chapter 9. Practicing the piano.
    </p>

    <h2>Elsewhere</h2>

    <p>
      <a href="https://github.com/parrik">github.com/parrik</a>
      &nbsp;·&nbsp;
      <a href="https://github.com/parrik/know-thyself">know-thyself scaffold (MIT)</a>
      &nbsp;·&nbsp;
      <a href="/rss.xml">RSS</a>
    </p>

    <p class="postscript">
      <em>Written by AI, lived by human.</em>
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .about { max-width: var(--max-width); }
  .about .lede {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .about p {
    margin: 0 0 1.1rem 0;
  }
  .about h2 {
    font-family: system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-top: 2.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .about .postscript {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 0.92rem;
  }
</style>
